I'm the kind of guy that knows when's he's had enough. 

I've seen a thing or two believe it or not. Yeah I'm young but why does that make a difference. Me, well I'm 15 but most people say I'm 17. I guess since I like to not shave and my beard is pretty good I'd say. But forget about the beard were talking about things I've seen. Yeah the end of days, that's what I hear people call it on the streets but it don't seem any different than before. I've heard stories from old men who say that back then, there were wars too. People didn't give a crap and the government was corrupt. Man it sounds just like today's day and age I'd tell them. But they never listen to me. I tell em that I know how to fix it all but they never listen to me. If only they gave me the chance to talk and take control I know I can fix all this, but no I'm just some dumb punk. Anyways, me I'm jole and I work with the FEU. Well technically I'm an underling but hey Im still getting paid for what I do. And guess what I actually like what I do. See this is how it all goes. Counties fight. Sometimes my county wins and we'll sometimes they lose but for me it dont matter. I just go about doing my job since it ain't no difference to me if we win or lose. It's not like I get a basket of treats if we win but the opposite is true too, ain't nobody give me lip if we lose either. My job, it's basically a janitor if you can imagine a janitor who cleans up after large battles. Sometimes I hide a thing or two and take it to my private stash. Right now I have a really cool things. Most of them are busted but one day I'll get them working. Make myself a bonfide tech suit, well only minuture sized but hey who's comparing sizes. I have the duty to go out after the battles and clean up ferrous junk. Most of it is spent ammunition and slags of ferrous chunks but since I'm the lowest jwlanitor I basically have to pick up stuff with my hands and place it in the hauler. My division is the east-gate team. We focus on ammunition and various other junk but my favorite part is seeing the techs walk by. Man the whole ground shakes and you can just see the power those things have. Our country has sevwr techs. Some of them are actually pretty good. The best one is shwain. He is a tech maniac. He will often put himself into danger then to cause a surprise attack and win. His tech is massively huge and his speciality is using the ripper rounds. Those are propoetary. If I told you how they worked I'd have to kill you. Ha, I'm justkidding. Technically I'm not supposed to know but most of the time the big guys like schwain will boast about things and I was at the right time and place when I overheard how the ripper ammunition worked. Man you should have been there. I love geography jokes. Basically the rippers are made from super-ferrous material. Super strong and super dense but also lightweight. It's very important for us to retrieve them after they have been shot. 

Then there is the smokers or the Cubans as most people call them. They burn so hot when shot that there will be basically nothing left to salvage except for the soon to be dead tech that had the disliberty of standing in the way of those things. Usually one one can be shot out of a gun since it would normally melt it if it were shot twice. 

Our country does pretty well. Since we are made from New-American muscle we have the pride and the power. But the ones that have given us trouble is Oceania. They have really been expanding their power and taking spoils from the principalities of Eurasia they have won. Currently the map is like this. All of North America is still run by New-America as it has been for the last 20 years. New-America hits the tip of Canlaska to most of Panmexico. The small island of Hawaii are lost to Oceania but we never really had a chance to hold on to those. The Caribbean islands are a mixed bag there too. Since we have won the most battles verses the lowered Panmexico and Argenzil we have claim to those islands. Getting absorbed into another county isn't too bad really. Mostly it determines your trade routes which are honored by all parties but then you have the rogues. Theses guys play by their own rules and well they don't win often but have been know to catch counties off guard and win a piece of land or two. These guys are ruthless and often don't care for the well being of their people. No one want to be connected to them. As for me when we do have battles they are amazing to see. It's basically a world event. People gamble away their life savings at these things and it can get people bad but it's the house that always wins since even if the country they belong to lose, they just swap their allegiance and people go and bet at them on the next battle. 

Like I said I plan on battling in one of those Mechs one day. Believe me I know all the moves. You never go for the main opponent he is way to big and will often have great armor. No you need to make sure your tactics are the best. 

One one battles are what they are all about. 

Large scale battles are ok but I'm the one having to clean the aftermath where we are putting in double and sometimes triples shifts.  

See every year they have tryouts. Anybody and everyone has a chance to to be a mech pilot. If you have the cash you can actually use similar vr tools that the mech riders use to get you that much closer to winning a chance, but one set alone costs more than a house. No for me it's all about the footage and my secret stash of mech gear. I've almost practically make a cockpit. Im missing a few finger nodes and the power unit but apart from that, just interacting with the cockpit I am pretty darn sure I know exactly what each button does.  Like this red one for example. It activates the module that then is a relay for the compression node. The compression node is the inturn engaged to  Rotate the enhance harmonic valve ...  I'm just kidding I have no idea what that red button does but I'm sure it does something pretty cool. You are only allowed to be a pilot when you are sixteen. Something about it being a nod to when teenagers where allowed to pilot cars before all ferrous materials were confiscated from everyone. Basically the only metal I see being used are the extraction vehicles and the mechs, and well the stuff I manage to smuggle out of the battle fields. Since my territory is the west I get to see the oceania battles but never the panamexico or indoeuro battles. Something about how we have to focus on our area and not be distracted by the other places. Seems pretty dumb to me but whatever. 

I never knew my dad or my mom but I think I've grown up pretty ok. 

The extraction units are large massive vehicles that we use to pick up the metal. They have massive rear containers that the loader units can pick up and dump into. There smaller containers on the side that you can put the smaller material that the L-Us can't pick up. That's my job. Its hard work but I'm dang good at it too. Put a little in the container, put a little in my pocket, its a win-win. Actually its a win-win-win since the country wins, I win, and one day when i build the baddest unit, we'll all win. 

Do I have any family, no but I do have a sister sort of. She is sister from another mister as I always say, but were close. I like her alot but when I tried to put a move on her bam she put me in the friend zone. She told me that she didn't want to ruin our friendship with a relationship but I was like dude you know what the best kind of ship a, relation-ship. yeah she laughed at that one and told me i was a dork. I know she has the hots for me but I respect her too much to hurt what we got here. 

Anyways see I have been in the west quadrant for aslong as i can remember. some people say that i might have some panamexican blood in me but i dont see it. to me everyone looks the same. we are all people trying to scrape by a living in this crappy world. 

Shiela has a weird accent. She says she is from oceania when new america took it over. her family migrated here and she has been here ever since. Her parents were radicals to the oceania and were sent to prison to work in a containment camp. Sheila was able to get away but she had to change her identity. man she had to grow up fast much like me but at least she had parents.
